snippet.textDisplay: Actually that car was £50k as a poverty spec 'eight' in 1980. Their's was most likely over £100k in 1990 making it over £220k in 2019 money. They are 'cheap' because maintenance costs are in line with those of £220k cars today. Say a normal car needs a sill done at £350 for example. £3500 on this. BUT look at the mot history. This car had advisories on a shock absorber wearing out. 3 of the 4 wheel bearings needing doing. 3 of the 4 brakes wearing thin and the power steering starting to leak. £5000 until the mot runs out then maybe get the money back in parts. A 'project Bentley' is a money pit.
